Webseeds are a great way to kick-start your torrents, especially if low numbers of peers are expected. It's a hybrid engine that runs both HTTP and the Torrent protocol all at once. 
&nbsp;
On a site like Kopy-Kate, a lot of videos are going to be made and edited by our users, and thus not everybody will be able to pull off 5-10 seeds at once. Usually the torrents that get the most seeds are the ones that have the greatest demand, such as the latest film premieres and TV shows.
&nbsp;
DropBox is a great way to webseed your torrents. WebTorrent will only webseed video files that are hosted on a server that has CORS enabled, and luckily, for us - DropBox happens to be CORS enabled!
&nbsp;
Having said that, DropBox may one day stab us in the back, so webseeds should only be used if you absolutely hate seeding, or cannot seed your videos, be it due to limited bandwith, slow internet speeds, slow computer, etc. We might even one day look into partnering up with Kim Dot Com at https://mega.nz/, who knows.

